children.text: There has not been adequate support for the flexible ductwork to prevent them from sagging.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 4254 – Ductwork for air-handling systems in buildings, Part 1: Flexible duct, requires in section 2, clause 2.5.3 that
‘Hangers shall be adequately attached to the building structure’
‘Support spacing’s shall not be greater than 1500mm apart and shall not have greater than 40mm/m of sag per support spacing. (See Figure 2)’ ;
Additional hangers should be installed to ensure that all ductwork is adequately supported.
